post_text:
Good Friday Afternoon Warriors! We all knew this day would come, but we have our first confirmed cases of COVID in our district. There is one staff member at the elementary and one student at the high school that have received positive tests; however, because of procedures and protocols we have in place, and in coordination with Three Rivers Health Department, we have significantly minimized any potential exposure to others in our buildings. Unless you have been contacted directly, your student or staff member is not considered to be at high-risk for exposure. We will continue operating as we have for the first 2.5 weeks of school.

I would implore everyone to encourage your students to continue abiding by the practices in place at school. They are working. Further, by practicing social distancing and masks outside of school, we increase our opportunities to keep the doors open for students throughout the year. The school year is off to a great start and we love seeing the students in our buildings. Stay safe, stay healthy, and have a great weekend!

Brandon Lavaley, Superintendent

post_text:
Hey WHS students!

Miss you all and thought I'd check in with a few announcements, a message and another song! I'm still not American Idol quality. But, if this isolation lasts long enough, someone might come up with an Old Guy American Idol show - one where the contestants have to wear name tags to remember who they are, hit mostly right notes and sign most of the lyrics correctly. If that happens, I'm GOLDEN!!!!!!!

Stay safe! Stay positive! Stay in touch!
Mr. Harris

text:
Hey WHS students!

Miss you all and thought I'd check in with a few announcements, a message and another song! I'm still not American Idol quality. But, if this isolation lasts long enough, someone might come up with an Old Guy American Idol show - one where the contestants have to wear name tags to remember who they are, hit mostly right notes and sign most of the lyrics correctly. If that happens, I'm GOLDEN!!!!!!!

Stay safe! Stay positive! Stay in touch!
Mr. Harris

DoubtMeNow 041720

post_text:
WHS National Honor Society will sponsor a Red Cross Blood Drive TOMORROW (Wednesday, Jan. 22) from 8:00 a.m. - 2:00 p.m. Walk-ins are welcome, or you can sign up at redcrossblood.org.

NHS will serve a hot breakfast to scheduled donors from 8:00 - 10:30 a.m.

The American Red Cross provides scholarship money to Wahoo students based on the number of blood donations collected throughout the year. Please support the Red Cross and our graduating students by joining us tomorrow! Thank you! #ExcellenceEverywhere
